definitions: act of defeating and taking control of a territory through military force
successful mastery or overcoming of something difficult or challenging
examples: The conquest of the region lasted several years
His military conquest changed the political landscape forever
Learning the violin was her greatest conquest
The mountain climber celebrated his conquest of Everest

definitions: Spanish or Portuguese soldier who conquered territories in the Americas during the 16th century
examples: The conquistador explored vast territories in South America
Many conquistadors sought gold and glory in the New World

definitions: person who is required by law to serve in the military forces
examples: The young conscript received basic military training
Many conscripts served during the wartime draft

definitions: compulsory enrollment of people for military service, typically during wartime or national emergency
examples: The government announced conscription for all eligible citizens
Many countries abolished conscription after the war ended

definitions: solemn religious ceremony of dedicating something or someone to a sacred purpose or divine service
examples: The consecration of the new cathedral drew thousands of worshippers
The priest performed the consecration with great reverence

definitions: organization or area designated for the protection and preservation of natural resources or wildlife
examples: The nature conservancy manages several protected wetlands
She works for a marine conservancy protecting coral reefs

definitions: person who actively works to protect and preserve the natural environment and wildlife
examples: The conservationist fought to save endangered species
Many conservationists oppose the new development project

definitions: political belief favoring traditional values and opposing radical change in society
tendency to prefer established practices and resist new ideas or methods
examples: His conservatism influenced his views on social policy
The party's conservatism appeals to traditional voters
The company's financial conservatism helped it survive the recession
Her conservatism in investing protected her savings

definitions: professional who preserves and restores valuable objects like artwork or historical items
person legally appointed to manage the affairs of someone unable to do so
examples: The museum conservator carefully restored the ancient painting
She trained as a conservator specializing in textile preservation
The court appointed a conservator for the elderly woman
The conservator managed his finances during his illness

definitions: institution specializing in the study and training of music and performing arts
room with glass walls and roof for growing plants attached to a house
examples: She studied violin at the prestigious conservatory
The conservatory graduates many talented musicians each year
They grew exotic plants in their sunny conservatory
The Victorian house featured a beautiful glass conservatory

definitions: thick sweet food made from fruit cooked with sugar to preserve it
examples: She spread strawberry conserve on her morning toast
The homemade apricot conserve won first prize at the fair

definitions: batch of goods sent or delivered to someone for sale or storage
arrangement where goods are sold on behalf of the owner who retains ownership until sold
examples: The consignment of electronics arrived at the warehouse
They received a large consignment from their overseas supplier
The boutique sells designer clothes on consignment
She placed her vintage jewelry on consignment at the antique shop

definitions: quality of always behaving or performing in a similar way over time
quality of forming a unified whole without contradictions or variations in logic
examples: The chef maintained consistency in every dish served
Her consistency in training led to athletic success
The consistency of his arguments convinced the jury
We need consistency between our policies and actions

definitions: comfort received by someone after a loss or disappointment, making them feel better
examples: Her kind words provided consolation during difficult times
The consolation prize softened the disappointment of losing

definitions: flat surface containing controls or switches for operating electronic equipment or machinery
decorative table or cabinet designed to stand against a wall
examples: The pilot checked instruments on the airplane console
She adjusted the sound levels on the mixing console
The antique console held family photographs and flowers
They placed a marble console in the entrance hall

definitions: process of combining several things, especially companies or departments, into one unit
action of making something stronger or more solid by uniting parts
examples: The consolidation created one of the largest banks
After consolidation, the company reduced operational costs
The consolidation of power took several years
Debt consolidation helped simplify their monthly payments

definitions: pleasing combination of sounds occurring together in music or speech
state of agreement or harmony between things, ideas, or actions
examples: The consonance of the choir created beautiful music
Poets often use consonance to enhance their verses
His actions showed consonance with his stated beliefs
The consonance between theory and practice impressed researchers

definitions: speech sound produced by partially or completely blocking airflow through the mouth
examples: The letter B represents a consonant sound
English has more consonants than vowel sounds

definitions: spouse of a reigning monarch who does not rule in their own right
group of musicians, especially playing early music on period instruments
examples: The queen consort attended the state ceremony
Prince Philip was consort to Queen Elizabeth II
The baroque consort performed authentic Renaissance music
A consort of viols played at the medieval festival

definitions: association of several organizations or companies formed to undertake a project together
examples: The consortium bid for the construction project
Universities formed a consortium to share research resources

definitions: person who takes part in a conspiracy or secret plan to do something illegal
examples: The conspirators met secretly to plan their actions
Police arrested several conspirators in the fraud scheme

definitions: police officer of the lowest rank in some countries, especially in Britain
examples: The local constable patrolled the village streets
She reported the incident to the duty constable

definitions: police force of a particular district or region, especially in Britain
examples: The local constabulary increased patrols during the festival
He served in the constabulary for twenty years

definitions: quality of being faithful and dependable, remaining unchanged over time despite challenges
examples: Her constancy in friendship lasted through decades
The constancy of his support never wavered

definitions: group of stars forming a recognizable pattern in the night sky
impressive group or gathering of related people or things
examples: The constellation Orion is visible in winter skies
Ancient sailors navigated using familiar constellations
A constellation of celebrities attended the premiere
The company assembled a constellation of talented engineers

definitions: feeling of anxiety or dismay causing confusion and distress, typically at something unexpected
examples: The announcement caused consternation among the employees
To her consternation, the door was locked

definitions: medical condition where bowel movements become difficult or less frequent than normal
examples: The doctor prescribed medication for chronic constipation
Dietary changes can help relieve constipation naturally

definitions: geographical area whose voters elect a representative to a legislative body
body of voters or supporters who have common interests or concerns
examples: The politician campaigned throughout her constituency
Each constituency elects one member of parliament
The senator's main constituency includes small business owners
Environmental groups form an important constituency for the party

definitions: part or element that combines with others to form a whole
voting member of a constituency who is represented by an elected official
examples: Water is a constituent of many chemical compounds
Each constituent element plays a vital role
The representative met with constituents at the town hall
Many constituents contacted their senator about the issue

definitions: action of making something narrower or tighter by squeezing or compressing
uncomfortable feeling of tightness or pressure in part of the body
examples: The constriction of blood vessels can raise blood pressure
Road constriction caused severe traffic delays
She felt a constriction in her throat when nervous
The constriction around his chest made breathing difficult

definitions: snake that kills prey by coiling around and squeezing it
muscle that tightens or closes an opening in the body
examples: The boa constrictor wrapped around its prey
Constrictors are found in tropical regions worldwide
The constrictor muscles control the pupil size
Throat constrictors help with swallowing food

definitions: person or company that builds or constructs buildings and structures
special method in programming that creates and initializes objects
examples: The constructor completed the project on schedule
They hired an experienced constructor for the renovation
The class constructor initializes all the variables
Every object needs a constructor function

definitions: official appointed by a government to live in a foreign city and protect citizens' interests
examples: The consul helped citizens renew their passports abroad
She contacted the British consul for assistance

definitions: office or building where a consul works to assist citizens in a foreign country
examples: They visited the consulate to obtain travel visas
The American consulate provides emergency services to citizens

definitions: professional practice of providing expert advice to organizations for a fee
examples: She started a management consultancy after retiring
The consultancy specialized in digital transformation strategies

definitions: formal meeting to discuss something or seek expert advice, especially with a professional
examples: The doctor scheduled a consultation for next week
After consultation with experts, they revised the plan

definitions: social and economic system encouraging the purchase of goods and services in large amounts
movement advocating for the rights and interests of consumers
examples: Critics argue consumerism damages the environment
Holiday shopping reflects the peak of consumerism
Consumerism led to stronger product safety laws
Ralph Nader championed consumerism in the 1960s

definitions: point at which something is complete or finalized, especially a marriage or business deal
examples: The consummation of the merger took several months
Years of planning led to the consummation of their dream

definitions: spreading of disease from one person to another by close contact
rapid spread of ideas, emotions, or behaviors through a group or population
examples: Quarantine measures prevented contagion in the hospital
The contagion spread quickly through the crowded school

Social media accelerates the contagion of trends

definitions: action of keeping something harmful under control or within limits to prevent spreading
examples: The containment of the oil spill required immediate action
Disease containment measures proved effective during the outbreak

definitions: substance that makes something impure or unsuitable by contact or mixture
examples: Tests revealed contaminants in the water supply
The factory released dangerous contaminants into the air

definitions: process of making something impure or harmful by exposure to polluting or poisonous substances
examples: Contamination of the food supply caused widespread illness
They tested the soil for chemical contamination

definitions: action of thinking deeply and carefully about something for a long time
form of prayer or meditation focusing on spiritual matters
examples: After much contemplation, she accepted the job offer
The garden provided a quiet space for contemplation
The monks spent hours in silent contemplation
Religious contemplation brought her inner peace

definitions: feeling that someone or something is worthless and deserves no respect or consideration
examples: His contempt for the rules got him expelled
She looked at him with obvious contempt

definitions: person or team competing for a championship or prize with a good chance of winning
examples: The young boxer emerged as a serious contender
Several contenders vie for the party leadership

definitions: prolonged argument or state of heated disagreement about something important
position of having a chance to win in a competition or contest
examples: The issue became a source of contention between neighbors

The team remained in contention for the playoffs
Three candidates are in contention for the award

definitions: state of happiness and satisfaction with one's situation in life
examples: She found contentment in simple daily pleasures
His face showed deep contentment with his achievements
